HEADWORD: Pentelican
<hw>Pen*tel"i*can</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to Mount
Pentelicus, near Athens, famous for its fine white marble quarries;
obtained from Mount Pentelicus; <as>as, the <ex>Pentelic</ex> marble of
which the Parthenon is built</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pentene</ent>⟦br⟧
